FBIS3-57000 "drsov015_f_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 National Affairs Kravchuk To Maintain Constitution on Crimea LD2101132794 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2210 GMT 20 Jan 94 LD2101132794 Kiev UNIAR Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Kiev, 20 January -- [passage omitted] Answering a question on whether he would use the right granted to him by the constitutional amendment adopted today allowing him to cancel acts by the Republic of the Crimea's bodies of executive power should they contravene Ukrainian laws and presidential directives, Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk said: If Crimea's bodies of power violate the constitution and laws of Ukraine, including the law of Ukraine on delimiting powers between Ukraine and the Crimea, I will undoubtedly bring all actions by Crimean authorities into accordance with state interests.
